{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_elk_ver01/data/sn85032933/00202192828/1908053001/1197.xml":{"full_text":"Saturday, May 30, 1908\nBASE. BALL.\nStanding of the Border City League.\nPlayed. W.\nDiamond N s 8 5\nfcociAl.K Kkoh... 7 4\n'o(jalkh Nationals 7 3\nVkkih .4 1\n1..\n3\n4\n3\n1 erf t.\n025\n680\n435\n250\nNOGALES NOTES.\nSunday Messrs. Y E. Balcom,\nnKUiiigrr of I he Salero mines, Doc\ntor Crepitj of Tucson, who is visit\ning in Patagonia, A. E. Crepin and\nVnl Y'alenzuela Jr., of Pataguniji,\nwent over to fluachuca on a hunt\ning and (bhing excursion. They\nreported a very enjoyable outing\nand much game.\nTomorrow Mnjor J. II. Stout will\ngo to San Bernardino, California,\nwit Ii the expectancy of remaining\nin that vicinity so-ue months. The\nrm'.jor has made his home in No-\ngales several years, and has made\nhere many warm friends who will\nrecollect him always with pleasure,\nand welcome him heartily when he\nreturns.\nV. N. Lester, Schuyler Case and\nCharles Smith, the stone anil cem\nent masons, have heen engaged\nthis week in laying cement Hours\nin the portico of the Club House,\nat the corner of Sonoita nvenue\nand Crawford streets, which prop\ntrty is owned by Bracey Curtis and\noccupied now by Mrs. Bailey's\nboarding hnuse.\nThe cement walks on the third\nblock or Crawford street are all\ncompleted except in front of the\nISiru property at the corner of West\navenue, and on that Barney Quinn\nlias finished the grading. Next\nweek be will build n retaining wall,\nand the week following Smith\nLester will lay the concrete. In\nthe block above the work of grad\ning the Schuckman and Jones\nproperties is well under way.\nThere is where the heaviest work\nhas been done, and many yards of\nearth has been removed.\nThursday the ladies of the Cur\nrent Topics Club gathered at the\nresidence of Mrs. Allen T. Bird, on\nCrawford street, in honor of Miss\nBeulah Smithson, one of the lead\ning members of the organization,\nwho will go east next week to teach\nin the summer normal school of Vir\nginia. The occasion was in the\nnature of surprise to the lady, who\nwas visibly affected by the man\nifested evidence of esteem in which\nfhe is held. As a token of remem\nbrance the departing lady was\npresented with an elegant silver\nCounted toilet set.\nSunday morning a thirteen-year-?ld\nboy named Manuel Verdugo,\njn an attempt to board the yard\nlocomotive, near the round house,\nslipped and fell beneath the wheels,\nbolb legs being crushed. lie was\ntaken to the Sisters' hospital im\nmediately, and Doctors Chenoweth\nand Purdy were called to attend\ntn poor lad. Within fifteen min\nxes after reaching the hospital he\nbecame unconscious, and half an\nhur afterward he died from the\nnock. All the. Hnr.tnra fWrl rln\nJvl;d nothing. It is reported that\nuoy came from Alamos.\nBoard of Tfdt,\nTh rrguUr meeting of the Board\nof Trade wh held a uual at tli\nBoard of Trade room Tuesday\nevening with a good attendance o'f\ndirectors present.\nOne of thn matters which came\nbefore the Board was presented in\na letter from the Geological Survey\nat Washington, slating lhat the\nuovernmriu would not be able to\nmaintain longer the gauging sta\ntion on the Santa Cruz River. This\nis an important matter to this\nsection, and it may become neces-\nsary for the Board of Trade to\nagain take charge of the expense!\nfor maintenance of such a station.)\nAt present the work of gauging has\nbeen discontinued i\nIt is noticeable that the\nBoard of Trade is rapidly being\npitted noon the mailing list of all\ncommercial organizations through\nout the country, as is shown by the\ntact that no movement of any im\nportance is inugurated by any of\nthem without this organization re\nceiving an invitation to participate.\nJust lately the Board has received\ntwo such invitations, one from ihe\nCalifornia Protection Committee,\nasking the endorsement of the\nBoard of a petition to the Secretary\nof the Navy for a greater arm\nament on the Pacific Coast, and\nanother from the organization in\nSt. Louis which is endeavoring\nto hasten the return of prosperity.\nThe Board, is in receipt of a letter\nfrom the Secretary of the Califor\nnia Promotion Committee stating\nthat the petition lately presented\nto Secretary Metealf has made a\ngreat impression upon him, and it\nis likely that good results will\nfollow.\nThe 4th of July Committee chair\nmen held a meeting immediately\nafter adjournment of the Board,\nand the hi nance committee was\nable to report a suftkient amount\nalready pledged to the committee\nto enahle the plans for a rousinr\ncelebration to be carried to a suc\ncessful completion. The advertis\ning committee of the 4th of July\ncelebration is in receipt of a large\nnumber of huge posters to be put\nin all the towns in this vicinity.\nand as the railroad company has\npromised a one-fare rate from\n(Jmymn nd all intermediate\npfwtion, It I likely tl at Nognhi\nwill nee a huge crowd on the 4ih,\nItMilroad rale from point north\nof NogaJea will Le announced\nshortly.\nBANCO DE SONORA.\nHERMOSILLO.\nBALANCE pkacticado el 30 de Abril de 1908.\nACTIVO,\nI I .II l A T f.\nu ineiaut-o, uncina uemrai y sucursalen; en Oro t f.OT.Vtooo\nPe Fuerit-s -i'\nMoiieda IrarHonHria Smiw\nBluet .ivotro- hhiicoi h'w'.w $1,215,247.2?.\nfcxisteucia eu nartera\nPrestmnoi nohre preudas 'u-.iS\nPrmamo hi potecarioti nl-tmivt\nInversiones en fondo publicon y aceiones 71\nluiuueoiea VtMlAl\nI y.X(-2,74(U7\nPASIVO.\nCapital social i nnn nn\nBilleteseu circulaeion 'Jwffi\nDupositos reembolsablea a la vista i'Sti vi\nFondo de reserva J' f'\"\nFondo de prevision III tlli'Xh\nHERMOSILLO. 30 DE ABRIL DE 1908.\nPEDRO MONTKVKRDK, MAY Mm r if R\nIntervener. H J. SMITH. A. F.TARLN, Lrente\nOontador Caiero.\nTHE PLEASURE DOUBLED\nTHE COST REDUCED\nZON-O-PHOIME\nTALKING MACHINES\nStven Tapering-Arm Models. $20 to $75.\nPlar Longerf, Lsr Longetf, Don'r Sent A.\nOn SPEAKING TERMS\nREG.U.S.PAT.OFFICE\nNEW RECORDS FOR MAY.\nROGERS CANDY COMPANY\nSELLING 